<br>
Gothakmithan's Testament Of Vanear Guide <br>
This is a simple two-part quest for a great +10 wisdom item: <br>
<br>
1. Seek out Moodoro Finharn, who is at Crows in North Qeynos. Ask him about The<br>
   Testament of Vanear. Give him 2 gold and you will receive a book which has two inventory<br>
   slots and a combine button in it. Then, give him 4 gold until you get the Jester Card from him.<br>
   Give the Jester Card back to him and he will give you page 34 of the Testament. Sell all the<br>
   other cards to a merchant. You now need page 30. <br>
2. You need to go to Highpass now. From Qeynos you will need to go Q. Hills-&gt; West<br>
   Karana -&gt; North Karana -&gt; East Karana -&gt;Highpass. Once you zone infrom East Karana<br>
   head toward the Kithikor zone. You will eventually see water on your right with a bridge<br>
   spanning it. Jump in the water, swim under the bridge, and go underwater. You will see an<br>
   underwater tunnel on your right. Swim through there and follow the right wall until you reach<br>
   another underwater passage. Swim through this short passage [note: being a barbarian I had to<br>
   duck a few times while swimming to get through this tiny hole] and you will come to dry land on<br>
   the other side. Run up and into the big open area. At the back of the big open area on the right<br>
   you will see a forge where the NPC with page 30 spawns, Dyllin Starsine [note: he is wearing a<br>
   Highhold Pass guard's uniform], a +/- 19th warrior. He has a 7 1/2 hour spawn cycle (learned<br>
   by camping him). Killing him is easy but the smugglers, who were green and light blue to me at<br>
   24, will aid him if they are close by. I just rooted him and used direct damage to put him down<br>
   quickly. Get page 30 from his corpse. Place page 30 (from Dyllin) and page 34 (which you<br>
   received from giving the Jester card back to Moodoro) in the Testament of Vanear container<br>
   and hit combine. You now have a Testament of Vanear. <br>
This is all you need to do to get the Testament. Of course, realize that your faction has to be<br>
   good with the citizens and guards of Qeynos to do this quest. I did this quest at 25th lvl. <br>
Gothakmithan Theladiesman <br>
46th Shaman &lt;The Band of the Broken Bow&gt;, The Tribunal <br>
- Editor's note: Moodoro is most often found very close to Lt. Dagarok, a near 50, ill-tempered<br>
  SK whose Harm Touch alone will insta-kill any shaman below 24th level. Know your exits -<br>
  Thantu <br>
